#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/security-architecture-concept.adoc:12
msgid "The Quarkus Security architecture provides several built-in authentication mechanisms. The `HttpAuthenticationMechanism` interface is the main entry mechanism for securing HTTP applications in Quarkus. Quarkus Security is also highly customizable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/security-architecture-concept.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "Overview of the Quarkus Security architecture"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/security-architecture-concept.adoc:16
msgid "When a client sends an HTTP request, Quarkus Security orchestrates security authentication and authorization by interacting with several built-in core components including `HttpAuthenticationMechanism`, `IdentityProvider`, and `SecurityIdentityAugmentor`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/security-architecture-concept.adoc:18
msgid "The sequential security validation process results in one of three outcomes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/security-architecture-concept.adoc:20
msgid "The HTTP request is authenticated and authorized and access to the Quarkus application is granted"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/security-architecture-concept.adoc:21
msgid "The HTTP request authentication fails and the requester receives a challenge"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/security-architecture-concept.adoc:22
msgid "The HTTP request authorization fails and and the requester's access to the Quarkus applicaton is denied"
msgstr ""

